{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only-- I was only on the ground-- periodically, the pilots would be sent to the ground troops as forward observers, and-- and be direct-- be controlling the-- the airplanes from the ground.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we would be with the-- the-- the combat troops, so right out there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you had to kind of rotate, you know, everybody had to take a turn at this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was-- this was really not much fun because, you know, you're really-- you're seeing stuff that you didn't have any idea was happening when you were in the air.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you're seeing prisoners taken.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You're seeing-- in one instance, I saw it was FFI, freedom fighters, a French patrol with assigned-- were assigned to this unit as foreign observers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were patrolling at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They captured some Germans, brought them back, questioned them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was a major, an American major that was in charge.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And these French guys cut off the right hands of two of the-- of the Germans and turned them loose, didn't put a tourniquet or anything on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Just they-- they question them and got what they wanted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think there were five altogether.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they just chopped off the right hands and turned them loose.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and I-- I-- that really got to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I went to the major and asked why the hell he didn't try to stop that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because-- that's one reason why we never-- if we shot an airplane down, we never went for the pilot in the parachute because the next time it could be us in the parachute.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they could come and they could tear you to ribbons.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, you're helpless, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
